<!--135-->Desperate Defense of the Ring x4<br>
<!--867-->Enduring Evil x2<br>
Thin & Stretched x2    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Strategy:<br>
Bid 2. Two is the safest bid. If you win, go first, play Westfarthing, get Aragorn early, if at site 1 play him for the discount rate. Move slowly. Too much in the shadow pool will wreck your relatively small fellowship. Double move only to keep the game competitive; if your opponent gets out ahead far enough to slow all the way down and only move one site a turn after site 5, you&#39;re toast. You&#39;ll have a little bit of trouble dropping enough to stop him. Shadow side is all about the burdens, but first a few questions answered: I was asked why I don&#39;t play Hate. The answer is because I have relentless charge, and most people that have any archers have at least two. So I exert one vitality two Mordor orc who could potentially stomp someone in combat thanks to Enduring Evil, or I exert a vit. 3 or 4 Nazgul to wound as many as 2 or three companions. Sometimes it&#39;s useless, but Hate is generally useless until after site 6 anyway. That having been said, Shadow side is all about adding burdens; I know, Athelas can slow down the process, but once you get them up to 5 burdens they&#39;re toast; Enquea kills a companion or two, Toldea assigns Legolas to the slaughter, Nazgul swords are dmg. +1, Enduring evil allows your Sauron orcs to win just about any skirmish, you get the idea. Tower Assassins are great; they keep Shoulder Fire decks honest, and pick off that exhausted Elrond with still an extra vitality to play a Thin & Stretched....you get the idea. Have fun, and enjoy the idea, feel free to have some liberty with the idea, and if you end up with a killer deck from it, post it and let me see! </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
